# React layer

Thin wrappers only. No CSS imports in component files — styles come via `@rgrmdesign/rgrm-ds-css` dependency.

## Pattern

```tsx
import { buttonClassNames, type ButtonVariant } from '@rgrmdesign/rgrm-ds-core/button';

export function Button({ variant = 'primary', className, children, ...rest }: ButtonProps) {
  return (
    <button className={buttonClassNames(variant, className)} {...rest}>
      {buttonContent(children)}
    </button>
  );
}
```

- Extend the correct HTML element type (`ButtonHTMLAttributes`, etc.)
- Merge `className` via core `classNames()` — no inline styles
- Wrap text children in `*_LABEL_CLASS` span when the CSS expects it (see Button)
- Register: tsup entry, `package.json` export, barrel `src/index.ts`

Reference: `packages/react/src/button/Button.tsx`
